# Workflow Rules

## Mode-Aware Behavior
Check PROJECT_MODE in activity_log.md before proceeding.

PRODUCTION mode:
- Tests MUST be written before implementation (TDD).
- Target ≥90% coverage for all core logic.
- Update changelog.md for every meaningful change.
- Update activity_log.md at session end.

LEARNING mode:
- Prototyping permitted without prior tests.
- Add a # TODO: harden comment on every untested block.
- Document key findings in activity_log.md before closing session.

## Reference Before Acting
Always read these before generating new code or making structural changes:
- .cursor/instructions.md
- .cursor/architecture.md
- .cursor/roadmap.md

## Consistency Checks
- New features must align with roadmap.md. Flag drift explicitly.
- New dependencies must be added to pyproject.toml immediately.
- Architecture changes must be reflected in architecture.md before coding begins.

## Refusal Policy
Refuse any request that would:
- Violate security.mdc rules
- Skip tests in PRODUCTION mode without explicit user override
- Introduce unpinned dependencies
- Create files outside the established directory structure without justification
